<h3>Interaction Scenarios</h3>
<p>
	<u>Start Turn</u>: Tim ends his turn and the order progresses to Sam. Sam recognizes it is his turn because he is sitting next to Tim, and also because the screen is tinted Blue, his color. At the top of the screen he sees Start Turn, and begins there. Reading left to right he is reminded to check if he has enough resource cards to make a Star card, and to check his Scar cards to see what penalties he has. He does both, and remembers he cannot cross oceans this turn due to a scar card. He keeps this in mind when planning the rest of his turn.
</p>
<p>
	<u>Recruit Troops</u>: After checking his cards, Sam knows the next part of the turn is recruiting new units. He knows the program has calculated how many troops he gets each turn, so he glances at the screen and sees a large 12 in the middle, between the words “recruit“ and “troops”. Sam then places 12 units from his pile around the board.
</p>
<p>
	<u>End Turn</u>: After taking his turn Sam finishes his turn and moves to the end step. Glancing at the bottom of the screen he sees the “Territories Conquered” and remembers he hasn’t recorded his capture of Egypt this turn. He clicks on the box and presses the “E” key, causing a list with “East Africa, Eastern Australia, Eastern United States and Egypt” to appear. He presses the “G” key and the list narrows to just “Egypt”, which he clicks on, and the app shows “Took Egypt from Jamie [X]” below the box to indicate the change. He then reads onward, right of the box, to see a reminder to draw any coin/resource cards he earned. He remembers he earned 1 resource card and draws it. While he does so Tim reminds him to check for any end of turn scar cards. Sam does this, and remembering that this is the last part of his turn and the last thing in our app, presses space to advance the turn. Jamie picks up the dice and begins her turn.
</p>



