<p>
	We decided to go with layout 1. Layout 3 would require the user to click through a page for every step of their turn which would pull them away from the game. The other 2 display all information at once and so the user can just look at it to check for numbers or reminders. The horizontal layout is better, assuming that the user reads left to right, as they aren’t jumping through sections when they scan the screen. It’s also more readable, again assuming English or a similarly written language, as the text in the boxes won’t be compressed into lines of only a few words on a smaller screen.
</p>

